reviews.review_text:
I am on an amazing journey I am listening to every 1994 show in order, mining for gold. 

To my ears, this sounds like the best option among the AUDs. This show carries over some of the energy from the previous evening. All songs were performed well, with some real fire in the second half of Set 2.  

Set 1 Highlights: Peggy-O, Masterpiece.

Set 2 HIGHlights: China>Rider, New Speedway Boogie. Truckin' is not exactly perfect, but the outro into drums is very unique. Drums>Space is outstanding, along with the Other One that follows. It's one of the best of '94. Like Truckin', the Wharf Rat has some flaws, but the outro jam gets wild. Liberty for the election year.
